Sentencas: Ba1-xSrxCo0.8Fe0.2O3-delta (x = 0.3-0.9) perovskite oxides have been studied as cathode material for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells (IT-SOFCs).
Titulo: Thermal, electrical and electrochemical characteristics of Ba1-xSrxCo0.8Fe0.2O3-δ cathode material for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The structural characteristics, temperature dependent weight loss, thermal expansion, electrical conductivity, and electrochemical properties in combination with YSZ electrolyte together with an SDC buffer layer were characterized by X-ray diffraction (XRD), thermogravimetric analysis (TG), dilatometry, DC four probe conductivity measurement and electrochemical impedance spectroscopy (EIS) techniques respectively.
Titulo: Thermal, electrical and electrochemical characteristics of Ba1-xSrxCo0.8Fe0.2O3-δ cathode material for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: XRD study revealed the lattice parameter and unit cell volume decrease with increase in Sr+2 content at the A-site.
Titulo: Thermal, electrical and electrochemical characteristics of Ba1-xSrxCo0.8Fe0.2O3-δ cathode material for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: TEC and electrical conductivity were found to increase with increasing Sr+2 content.
Titulo: Thermal, electrical and electrochemical characteristics of Ba1-xSrxCo0.8Fe0.2O3-δ cathode material for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Electrical conductivity was found to be dependent on the thermal history of the samples.
Titulo: Thermal, electrical and electrochemical characteristics of Ba1-xSrxCo0.8Fe0.2O3-δ cathode material for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Polarization resistance of the samples with SDC buffered YSZ electrolyte decreased with increasing Sr+2 content which was ascribed to the higher conductivity with improved oxygen adsorption/desorption and oxygen ions diffusion processes.
Titulo: Thermal, electrical and electrochemical characteristics of Ba1-xSrxCo0.8Fe0.2O3-δ cathode material for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The intrinsic oxygen reduction reaction rate also increased with Sr+2 content at the A-site.
Titulo: Thermal, electrical and electrochemical characteristics of Ba1-xSrxCo0.8Fe0.2O3-δ cathode material for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The exchange current for intrinsic oxygen reduction reaction at 700 degrees C was found to be 50.0 mA cm(-2) for Ba0.3Sr0.7Co0.8Fe0.2O3-delta; a value which is about 50% higher than that for Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8Fe0.2O3-delta, a widely studied cathode material.
Titulo: Thermal, electrical and electrochemical characteristics of Ba1-xSrxCo0.8Fe0.2O3-δ cathode material for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Therefore, the present composition may be a potential cathode material for IT-SOFC application.
Titulo: Thermal, electrical and electrochemical characteristics of Ba1-xSrxCo0.8Fe0.2O3-δ cathode material for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells
